cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.AI 

The paper focuses on cybersecurity attacks and prevention in the vehicle-to-infrastructure (V2I) network, which involves communication between vehicles and infrastructure systems. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The development of a novel V2I cybersecurity architecture also involves software engineering (cs.SE) and system design (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for detecting cyberattacks suggests a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
